# Fragility (2011)

A feedback work for six untouched guitars, played by adjusting their amplifiers.

This is a work that explores feedback. Six guitars are placed on the ground next to
amplifiers. The guitars are never touched; the piece is played by adjusting the
amplifiers.

_Fragility_ begins by getting each instrument to feed back at low and controlled
volumes. The feedback from each instrument interacts with the others. Sine tones are
introduced to balance out the frequency range and to add more complex relations
between sounds. Eventually the volume increases to the point that the sound is mostly
informed by the physical characteristics of the room. By walking across the room, or
even slightly moving one's head, the audience can explore the sound of the room.
